<subSubSection lastPageId="63" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,1843,2013]" lastBlockId="63.[151,1436,151,501]" lastPageId="63" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,386,1843,1869]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Material examined.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[395,500,1843,1869]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Syntypes</typeStatus>
, male, two females, one pupa and three larvae were reared from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Basilicum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polystachyon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Basilicum polystachyon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Moench (as 
<taxonomicName authority="H.G.L.Reichenbach, 1829" authorityName="H.G.L.Reichenbach" authorityYear="1829" box="[433,715,1879,1905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Moschosma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polystachum">
<emphasis box="[433,715,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Moschosma polystachum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[error for 
<emphasis box="[830,984,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">polystachyum</emphasis>
] Benth). collected 
<date box="[1197,1284,1879,1905]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" value="1914-04">iv-1914</date>
at Semarang, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,203,1915,1941]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Java</collectingRegion>
, Felt #a2099. The series is on three slides and uncleared. The male is entire, mounted laterally, with shrunken terminalia; the slide contains additionally a cecidomyiine male with tricircumfilar antennae, ignored by both Felt and us here. The females are missing some wings and tarsi, antennae are shrunken but appear entire, ovipositors are extended and visible. The pupa is partially damaged. Of the three larvae, one is entire with the terminal segment filled with debris, one consisting only of a head and a spatula, and one is parasitized with only the spatula observable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,258,284]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[352,413,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Adult</emphasis>
. Wing R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[515,523,277,291]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">5</subScript>
bowed at distal third, joining C at wing apex, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1068,1076,277,291]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">1</subScript>
shorter than wing half, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1365,1374,277,291]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">S</subScript>
rudimentary, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[280,288,313,327]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">4</subScript>
and Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[373,381,313,327]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">1</subScript>
forming fork. Palpus 4-segmented [
<figureCitation box="[786,895,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[839,895,294,321]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="m" value="37.0">37m</quantity>
</figureCitation>
]. First tarsomere with small, straight ventro-apical lobe [
<figureCitation box="[253,347,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37j</figureCitation>
]. Tarsal claws simple, thin, bent at distal third, longer than empodia [
<figureCitation box="[1119,1212,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37i</figureCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis box="[199,257,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Male</emphasis>
. Wing length 
<quantity box="[413,501,366,393]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[582,670,367,393]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
. Flagellomeres 12, vaguely trinodal, circumfila strongly bowed [
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37k</figureCitation>
], gonocoxite with triangular ventroapical lobe, bearing long setae at apex, gonostylus twice as long as wide, bent and blunt distally, uniformly setulose, tooth on gonostylus not properly visible on available specimen [
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37h</figureCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" startId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" targetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" targetPageId="63">
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1436,1366,1534]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,554,1366,1390]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
FIGURES 37a–p. 
<taxonomicName box="[351,554,1366,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Schizomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodosa">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,554,1366,1390]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Schizomyia nodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
: a, gall on 
<taxonomicName box="[673,916,1366,1390]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Basilicum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polystachyon">
<emphasis box="[673,916,1366,1390]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Basilicum polystachyon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[789,800,1402,1416]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">th</superScript>
abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[653,668,1438,1452]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">nd</superScript>
abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[591,603,1474,1488]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">rd</superScript>
flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[301,313,1510,1524]" fontSize="6" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">rd</superScript>
flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,1580,2039]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Female</emphasis>
. Wing length 
<quantity box="[448,536,1581,1607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
(1.7–1.8), width 
<quantity box="[737,828,1580,1607]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
. Flagellomeres 
<quantity box="[1009,1067,1580,1607]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
both antennae of both available females, first and second fused, all with short necks, progressively shortened, with last flagellomere abruptly so, circumfila appressed to node [
<figureCitation box="[495,631,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Figs 37n, p</figureCitation>
]. Ovipositor long, thin, flexible, with small dorsobasal lobe [
<figureCitation box="[1328,1423,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37l</figureCitation>
]; needle-like part about 6x longer than seventh sternite, bearing minute, medially appressed cerci visible, each with a single lateral seta [
<figureCitation box="[379,479,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37o</figureCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,1580,2039]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis box="[199,258,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Pupa</emphasis>
. Length 
<quantity box="[361,451,1761,1787]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
. Antennal bases not produced, face without horns [
<figureCitation box="[1029,1129,1760,1787]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37e</figureCitation>
]; prothoracic spiracle long, about 10x longer than basal width, trachea ending at apex [
<figureCitation box="[807,903,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37f</figureCitation>
]; abdominal segments anterodorsally with large spiny spicules, otherwise mostly evenly covered with short spicules, on each side of terga a pair of closely set asetose papillae [
<figureCitation box="[306,406,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[360,406,1868,1895]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.7" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="g" value="37.0">37g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,1580,2039]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis box="[199,266,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Larva</emphasis>
. Length 
<quantity box="[365,453,1905,1931]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
. Spatula bilobed, lateral papillae comprising one pair of setose papillae and one triplet of two setose and one asetose papillae [
<figureCitation box="[561,661,1940,1967]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37c</figureCitation>
]; head with antennae 1.5x longer than wide at base, apodemes longer than head capsule [
<figureCitation box="[364,465,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37b</figureCitation>
]; cuticle of rounded verrucae throughout [
<figureCitation box="[935,1036,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 37" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,530,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-172@63.[151,1436,525,1343]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 37a–p. Schizomyia nodosa: a, gall on Basilicum polystachyon (Fig. 947 of DvLR &amp; DvL (1926)); b–d, larva: b, head (ventral); c, spatula with adjacent papillae; d, cuticle of 7th abdominal segment (ventrolateral); e–g, pupa: e, anterior segments (ventrolateral); f, prothoracic spiracle; g, 2nd abdominal tergum (dorsolateral); h–k, male: h, terminalia (lateral); i, tarsal claw and empodium; j, first tarsomere; k, 3rd flagellomere; l–p, female: l, postabdomen (lateral, arrow marks dorsobasal lobe); m, palpus; n, 3rd flagellomere; o. cerci; p, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406948/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 37d</figureCitation>
].
</paragraph>
